NOTE — Clinical safety disclaimer (separate from the MIT license terms above):

This software is a hackathon-stage prototype of a clinical-decision-support
research tool. It is NOT a regulated medical device. It has not been
evaluated by the FDA, MHRA, EMA, or any other regulatory body. It must not
be used to make real triage, diagnostic, or treatment decisions for real
patients without (1) clinician retention of independent review of the basis
for each output, (2) a completed prospective validation study at the
deploying institution, and (3) HIPAA/GDPR-compliant deployment with executed
Business Associate Agreements covering all third-party model and inference
processors.

Voice biomarker outputs (Helios, Apollo, Psyche profiles) are wellness-scope
signals, not regulated diagnostic outputs. Concordance flags are decision-
support hints, not diagnoses. ESI scoring is computed deterministically from
chief-complaint label and concordance flags; the LLM prose only narrates the
decision and is subject to known LLM failure modes (hallucination, drift,
prompt sensitivity).

The clinical evidence base (MIMIC-IV-ED CVD bias dictionary, peer-reviewed
voice-biomarker citations) is referenced for transparency. Clinical
deployment requires cross-institutional retrospective validation, prospective
study at the deploying ED, IRB approval, and FDA Clinical Decision Support
Software guidance review per the responsibilities of the deploying
institution.

Patients seeking medical care should not rely on this software for any
medical advice or care decision.
